President Obama has nominated Judge Christopher Droney for a seat on the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit. Judge Droney is currently serving as a United States District Judge for Connecticut. He has a distinguished career and is known for his excellence and integrity. Judge Droney was born and raised in West Hartford, Connecticut, and graduated magna cum laude from the College of the Holy Cross in 1976. He obtained his J.D. from the University of Connecticut School of Law in 1979. Before becoming a judge, he worked in private practice specializing in trial work and also served on the Town Council of West Hartford. In 1993, Judge Droney was appointed United States Attorney for the District of Connecticut and in 1997, he was nominated by President Clinton to the United States District Court for the District of Connecticut, where he has served since.